    public abstract class PrinterState_DPL
extends PrinterData_DPL
    This is the base class for the printer state code. This will handle configuration queries and settings and all of the shared routines for the sub-classes that each handle a specific printer query.

    • Method Detail

      • queryPrinter

        public void queryPrinter(int timeout)
                  throws java.lang.Exception
        This will query the printer to update the values for this set of parameters. All current values will be replaced with the values on the printer.

        Initially the PrinterState objects are empty. Use this to query them with the latest values from the printer. Unlink the other version of Update which takes the printer response string, this will handle all of the printer querying for you.

        Parameters:
        timeout - Maximum number of msec to wait for a response.
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception - error

      • update

        public void update(int timeout)
            throws java.lang.Exception
        This will re-query the printer to update the values for this set of parameters. All current values will be replaced with the values on the printer.

        Initially the PrinterState objects are empty. Use this to update them with the latest values from the printer. Unlink the other version of Update which takes the printer response string, this will handle all of the printer querying for you.

        Parameters:
        timeout - Maximum number of msec to wait for a response.
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception - error
